The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 29 November is 112,614 (12,979.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 24 November, there were 5,611 new confirmed cases (646.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 17 November, there were 4,973 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 13% (638 extra cases).
